##### MF4: ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS OF SECONDARY PARTICLES           8225 1451
                                                                  8225 1451
The versatility of MF6 for the storage of almost any secondary    8225 1451
distribution entails that we only use MF4 for the neutron elastic 8225 1451
scattering distribution. All data are generated with TALYS.       8225 1451
                                                                  8225 1451
- MT2      : Elastic angular distribution                         8225 1451
                                                                  8225 1451
The flag LTT=3 is used to indicate a switch at 20 MeV from a      8225 1451
Legendre representation to a tabulated representation. For        8225 1451
incident energies below 20 MeV, the Legendre coefficients are     8225 1451
given on a sufficiently precise energy grid. They are a sum of    8225 1451
calculated Legendre coefficients for compound nucleus and         8225 1451
shape-elastic scattering. For incident energies above 20 MeV,     8225 1451
relative angular distributions are tabulated on an angular grid.  8225 1451
                                                                  8225 1451
##### MF6: PRODUCT ENERGY-ANGLE DISTRIBUTIONS                     8225 1451
                                                                  8225 1451
In MF6 we store all secondary energy, angle, and energy-angle     8225 1451
distributions, as well as all residual and discrete + continuum   8225 1451
photon production cross sections. We thus do not use MF12-15 for  8225 1451
the photon production that accompanies each reaction. All data    8225 1451
are generated with TALYS.                                         8225 1451
                                                                  8225 1451
- MT5      : (n,anything) yields and energy-angle distributions   8225 1451
                                                                  8225 1451
For energies below 20 MeV, MT5 contains the relative yields of    8225 1451
the (n,gamma x) reaction, where x may represent neutron, proton,  8225 1451
deuteron, triton, Helium-3 or alpha. Using the (n,gamma x) cross  8225 1451
section of MF3/MT3, the (n,gamma p), ..., (n,gamma alpha) cross   8225 1451
section can be recovered. For energies above 20 MeV, MT5 contains 8225 1451
the production yields of particles and residual products. It also 8225 1451
contains the secondary energy-angle distributions for all         8225 1451
particles and photons. First, the yields for neutrons are given   8225 1451
for the whole energy range. Next, on a secondary energy grid the  8225 1451
relative emission spectra are given together with the parameters  8225 1451
for the Kalbach systematics for angular distributions. Inelastic  8225 1451
scattering cross sections for discrete states have been broadened 8225 1451
and added to the continuum spectra. This procedure is repeated    8225 1451
for protons, deuterons, tritons, Helium-3, alpha particles and    8225 1451
photons. Finally, the residual production yields are given per    8225 1451
final product. All these yields and relative distributions can    8225 1451
be multiplied with the cross sections given in MF3/MT5 to get     8225 1451
the production cross sections and (double-)differential cross     8225 1451
sections.                                                         8225 1451
