particle yields are given. Next, on a sufficiently dense incident 8225 1451
energy grid the secondary energy-angle distributions are          8225 1451
specified by means of the relative emission spectra and the       8225 1451
parameters for the Kalbach systematics for angular distributions. 8225 1451
Next, the photon yield is tabulated as a function of incident     8225 1451
energy. For each incident energy, the photon production is given  8225 1451
for all discrete gamma lines present in the final nucleus. A      8225 1451
continuum photon distribution is added to this. We assume         8225 1451
isotropy for all produced gamma rays.                             8225 1451
